videos.description: J.J Frazier gets the floater to go plus the foul, putting Georgia up 12-0 over Kentucky.
videos.headline: Georgia gets out to an early 12-0 run over Kentucky

videos.description: Prior to Brent Musburger's final television broadcast, John Calipari and Kentucky present him with a jersey.
videos.headline: Kentucky honors Musburger

videos.description: Georgia coach Mark Fox talks about improvements team needs to make in the 2nd half.
videos.headline: Georgia coach Mark Fox talks about how team needs to compete better on the glass

videos.description: Malik Monk gets the block and saves the ball, Isaiah Briscoe gets the layup on the other end.
videos.headline: Defense leads to offense with Briscoe layup for Kentucky

videos.description: Brent Musburger sets the stage for his final broadcast, getting the viewers prepared for Kentucky's matchup with Georgia.
videos.headline: Musburger welcomes the audience to his final broadcast

videos.description: Isaiah Briscoe uses his the nice move for the layin to give Kentucky a 6 point lead.
videos.headline: Briscoe uses the stop and go move for the strong layin

videos.description: Isaiah Briscoe throws the pass to Edrice Adebayo for the alley-oop slam.
videos.headline: Adebayo goes up high for the alley-oop

videos.description: Georgia's Jordan Harris gets defender in the air and then drains the 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Harris uses the fake to drain the wide open 3-pointer

videos.description: Malik Monk makes a  jumper that ties the game at 76. Georgia takes the ball to the other end and can't convert, giving Kentucky one more shot to win the game but misses at the buzzer forcing overtime.
videos.headline: Monk sends game to OT with jumper

videos.description: Malik Monk feeds Edrice Adebayo who finishes with the alley-oop slam for Kentucky in overtime.
videos.headline: Monk throws the lob to Adebayo to secure UK's OT win

videos.description: Brent Musburger receives a hug from John Calipari and Jay Bilas thanks him for his great career as a broadcaster.
videos.headline: Calipari, Bilas thank Musburger

videos.description: Brent Musburger says farewell to a legendary career and passes the reigns to the younger broadcasters.
videos.headline: Musburger signs off

videos.description: Brett Musburger's legendary broadcast career comes to and end with Malik Monk scoring 37 points and Kentucky prevailing past Georgia 90-81 in overtime.
videos.headline: Musburger's last call sees Kentucky victorious in OT

videos.description: Malik Monk scores just six points in the first half but takes over in the second and overtime, dropping 31 of his 37 and carrying Kentucky past Georgia to end the Wildcats' two game losing streak.
